"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code uses np.random.randint with dtype=bool, which is incorrect. The dtype should be np.bool_ or simply not specified, as np.random.randint generates integers, not boolean values. This will lead to unexpected behavior when using the mask in np.copyto.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8\\n< mask = np.random.randint(2, size=size, dtype=bool)\\n---\\n> mask = np.random.randint(2, size=size) > 0\"\n}"